---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout
  title="Tree Removal Erina | Arborist, Bushland Blocks & Hazard Reduction"
  description="Tree services in Erina — large removals, lopping & pruning, stump grinding and bushfire hazard-reduction by qualified arborists. Dense bushland blocks backing Strickland State Forest. Free quote."
  canonical="https://centralcoasttreeservice.com.au/erina/">
  <Fragment slot="head">
  </Fragment>

  <section class="hero">
    <div class="hero-inner">
      <span class="hero-eyebrow">Erina &middot; Erina Heights &middot; Green Point &middot; Kincumber</span>
      <h1>Tree services in <span class="accent">Erina</span>.</h1>
      <p class="hero-sub">
        Erina backs onto Strickland State Forest and the Brisbane Water bushland &mdash;
        densely treed blocks, big mature eucalypts, and properties on
        RFS-mapped bushfire-prone land. Large removals, crown work, stump grinding
        and bushfire hazard-reduction by qualified arborists. Free written quote on
        site.
      </p>
      <div class="hero-actions">
        <a class="ph-cta btn btn-primary" href="/quote/" aria-label="Call us"><span aria-hidden="true">&#9742;</span> <span class="ph-text">Tap to call</span></a>
        <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/quote/">Get a free quote</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <span class="section-eyebrow">Tree work in Erina</span>
      <h2>What we do around Erina.</h2>
      <div class="divider"></div>
      <div style="max-width: 65rem;">
        <h3>Bushland blocks &amp; big-tree removals.</h3>
        <p>
          Erina and its surrounds (Erina Heights, Green Point) include some of the
          most heavily treed residential blocks on the Central Coast, many backing
          directly onto <strong>Strickland State Forest</strong> and the
          surrounding reserves. That means tall, mature <strong>blackbutt, spotted
          gum, angophora and turpentine</strong> close to homes, and a steady demand
          for <strong>large, complex removals</strong> &mdash; dead and dangerous trees,
          trees overhanging a roof, and oversized eucalypts that need sectional
          dismantling or a crane rather than a straight fell. See
          <a href="/services/tree-removal/">tree removal</a> for how we take big
          trees down safely on a confined bushland block.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Bushfire hazard-reduction &amp; the 10/50 code.</h3>
        <p>
          Because so much of Erina sits on or beside <strong>bushfire-prone
          land</strong>, hazard-reduction is a real concern. Where your property
          falls inside the <strong>RFS 10/50 Vegetation Clearing Entitlement
          Area</strong> (check your address on the NSW Rural Fire Service online
          tool), the code lets you clear trees within 10m of a home and underlying
          shrubs within 50m, without separate Council approval, to create a
          defendable space. We confirm your eligibility against the RFS tool first,
          then carry out the work &mdash; see
          <a href="/services/land-clearing/">land clearing &amp; hazard-reduction</a>.
          Outside the entitlement, established trees stay protected and may need a
          Council Private Tree Works approval.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Pruning, deadwooding and storm work.</h3>
        <p>
          Living among big eucalypts means <a href="/services/tree-lopping/">deadwooding
          and crown thinning</a> to AS 4373 is ongoing maintenance &mdash; the dead and
          overextended limbs above a house are the ones most likely to come down in
          a blow. And when an East Coast Low hits the bushland edge, we run
          <a href="/services/emergency-tree-removal/">24/7 storm response</a> for the
          fallen trees and limbs that close driveways and land on roofs around Erina.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Typical Erina jobs.</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Crane-assisted removal of a large dead blackbutt threatening an Erina Heights home</li>
          <li>RFS 10/50 hazard-reduction clearing around a bushland-backed house (eligibility confirmed)</li>
          <li>Deadwooding mature spotted gums overhanging a Green Point roofline</li>
          <li>Selective clearing and mulching of a densely treed block for a new build</li>
          <li>Stump grinding after a multi-tree removal, mulch left on the bush block</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section-alt">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <h2>Other service areas.</h2>
      <div class="areas-grid">
        <a class="area-pill" href="/gosford/">Gosford</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/terrigal/">Terrigal</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/wyong/">Wyong</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/woy-woy/">Woy Woy</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/central-coast-region/">All Central Coast Region</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <div class="cta-block">
        <h2>Free Erina tree quote.</h2>
        <p>Bushland-block specialists. Large removals &amp; RFS 10/50 hazard-reduction. 24/7 storm response.</p>
        <div class="hero-actions" style="justify-content:center;">
          <a class="ph-cta btn btn-primary" href="/quote/" aria-label="Call us"><span aria-hidden="true">&#9742;</span> <span class="ph-text">Tap to call</span></a>
          <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/quote/">Book online</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
